[zero_shot][olmo3_7b_instruct][mmlu] sample 49/200 done id=mmlu_validation_338 prediction='The unknown chloride compound is dissolved in water and titrated with excess Pb(NO₃)₂. Pb(NO₃)₂ reacts with Cl⁻ ions to form PbCl₂(s):  \nPb²⁺ + 2 Cl⁻ → PbCl₂(s).  \nStoichiometrically, 1 mole of PbCl₂ is formed for every 2 moles of Cl⁻.  \nSince the precipitate (PbCl₂) mass is given as 0.0050 mol, this represents the moles of Pb²⁺ added (because Pb is in excess and only Cl⁻ from the sample limits the reaction).  \nEach mole of PbCl₂ contains2 moles of Cl⁻.  \nThus, moles of Cl⁻ in the original sample = 2 × 0.0050 mol =0.010 mol Cl⁻.  \nThe mass of Cl⁻ is moles × molar mass of Cl⁻ (or Cl as part of Cl⁻).  \nMolar mass of Cl⁻ ≈35.45 g/mol (using atomic mass of Cl).  \nMass of Cl⁻ =0.010 mol ×35.45 g/mol =0.3545 g' gold='B' correct=False
