[zero_shot][olmo3_7b_instruct][mmlu] sample 57/200 done id=mmlu_validation_433 prediction='Step 1: Julia\'s income is $1000 per week.  \nStep 2: Her marginal propensity to consume (MPC) is 0.5, meaning she spends 50% of any additional income.  \nStep 3: Since she already spends $30 regardless of income, her "additional" income to spend is $1000 - $30 = $970.  \nStep 4: She will spend 0.5 × $970 = $485 from her income.  \nStep5: Her savings are her income minus her total spending: $1000 (from income) + $30 (autonomous spending) - $485 (spending from income) = $1000 - $485 = $515.  \nWait, but that\'s not one of the options. Let me check the standard Keynesian savings formula.  \nThe Keynesian savings function S = Y - C, where C = a + cY (autonomous consumption + MPC × income).  \nHere, autonomous consumption is $30, MPC is 0.5, income is $1000.  \nSo C = 30 + 0.5×1000 = 30 + 500 = $530.  \nThen S = Y - (C - a)' gold='D' correct=False
